{
  "texts": [
    "Recently, researchers have focused more on large-scale decoder-only LLMs trained with next token prediction and instruction tuning (TYPE 2.A).",
    "Examples include ChemDFM (Zhao et al., 2024), ChemLLM (Zhang et al., 2024b), and LlaSMol (Yu et al., 2024a).",
    "Given the desired generalization capability of such models, they are evaluated on a diverse set of tasks such as name conversion (Kim et al., 2019), reaction prediction (Jin et al., 2017), retrosynthesis (Schneider et al., 2016), text-based molecule design (Edwards et al., 2022), and crystal generation (Antunes et al., 2023; Flam-Shepherd and Aspuru-Guzik, 2023; Gruver et al., 2024).",
    "Graphs are appropriate data structures for characterizing molecules (Jin et al., 2023a).",
    "Popular datasets containing molecular graphs include ChEBI-20 (Edwards et al., 2021 (Edwards et al.,, 2022)), ZINC (Sterling and Irwin, 2015), and PCDes (Zeng et al., 2022)."
  ]
}